author: Inside Edition
description: Country music icon Dolly Parton posted a video to social media with the caption, "I ain't dead yet!" Worries for Parton intensified Tuesday after her sister made a post pleading for prayers, leading to an outpouring of concern. It has been a difficult year for 79-year-old Parton. In March, her husband of nearly 60 years died. On September 17, she canceled an appearance at Dollywood due to an infection from a kidney stone.
title: Dolly Parton Clears the Air After Worries About Her Health

author: Inside Edition
description: Two unruly sisters were taken into custody after they were ordered off a Frontier Airlines flight because they appeared to be drunk. Police at Orlando International Airport found a stricken gate agent sprawled across the jetway. Cops arrested 22-year-old Kiera Lyons without too much trouble. But, when her 31-year-old sister, Maura saw her sibling being taken away, she had a meltdown. She was also arrested. The charges were later dropped.
title: Chaos Erupts As Cops Arrest Unruly Sisters At Orlando Airport

author: Inside Edition
description: Leigh Wainscott thought she had found true love when she met Jeffrey Manchester. Manchester told her he worked for the government. In reality, Manchester had just escaped from state prison. He was known as the infamous 'Rooftop Robber.' Authorities say he broke into dozens of McDonalds and other fast food restaurants through the roof. Manchester would force workers to hand over cash, before locking them in the freezer. Wainscott did not know who Manchester really was until the FBI told her.
title: The True Story Behind Channing Tatum's 'Roofman' Character

author: Inside Edition
description: Federal authorities say an Uber driver started one of the most devastating fires in Los Angeles history: The Palisades Fire. Jonathan Rinderknecht, 29, was taken into custody in Orlando, Florida, although authorities say he lived in the Palisades and was familiar with the area. He is suspected of first starting a smaller fire that burned underground, eventually erupting into The Palisades Fire. The arrest comes after a 9-month investigation.
title: Jonathan Rinderknecht Arrested For Allegedly Starting Palisades Fire

author: Inside Edition
description: Zach Bryan responded Wednesday to the growing backlash over his new song. He released a snippet of the song titled "Bad News," but it was enough to spark an outcry from MAGA world. Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem says she is boycotting Bryan. Her department made a new video trolling the singer. Bryan appealed to his fan base to say he's been "misconstrued." "When you hear the rest of the song, you will understand the full context," Bryan wrote on social media.
title: Singer Zach Bryan Speaks Out After Backlash Over ICE Lyrics

author: Inside Edition
description: Joyce D'Arcy wants to raise awareness after her husband suddenly died after coming in contact with a flesh-eating bacteria after a visit to a beach in Virginia.
title: Man Dies From Flesh-Eating Bacteria After Beach Visit #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: It's a great pumpkin! Tony Scott of Wappingers Falls, New York, has turned growing giant gourds into a hobby that he takes to competition. This year's pumpkin weighed in at 1931 pounds, which earned him third place, but how does a gardener achieve such a massive size? Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: New York Man Grows Pumpkin Weighing 1,931 Pounds For Competition

author: Inside Edition
description: Denise Richards testified in court that her ex, #AaronPhypers "would often threaten to throw me through the windows and off balconies. He's almost killed me so many damn times."
title: Denise Richards Divorce Battle Goes 'Nuclear' #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: We might all know “The Fate of Ophelia," but now we know the fate of our very own Alison Hall! She visited @bdcnyc this morning to learn the choreography for the Taylor Swift hit.
title: Inside Edition's Alison Hall Learns Taylor Swift 'Ophelia' Choreography #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: An Arizona school says it's in crisis not knowing if they will be able to feed their students. City View High School is a charter school in Phoenix. It only has about 50 students, but those who run the school say they haven't been able to find a consistent food supplier. The school says it doesn't qualify for the federal school lunch program. It also says nearly all of the students are low income and many can't afford to bring food from home. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Phoenix High School Struggles To Provide Lunch For Its Students

author: Inside Edition
description: Ciara Babcock from California has reunited with her dog, Opie, after he got lost and was found over 2000 miles away. In July, a bad storm scared Opie, and he got out of the yard. Ciara looked for him for months, but was giving up hope. Last week, she received a call from the Itasca Police Department saying he was safe at DuPage County Animal Services. Ciara booked the first flight across the country to reunite with her dog. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: California Dog Reunites With Owner After Being Found In Chicago

author: Inside Edition
description: A distraught husband called 911 after his wife took longer than usual on her nightly dog walk. The Okaloosa County Sheriff released this bodycam video from the responding deputy.  After getting information from the man, the deputy got in her car and went out looking for the missing elderly woman. It didn't take long for her to spot a sign of hope. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Dog Leads Sheriff's Deputy To Missing Grandma In Florida

author: Inside Edition
description: Police say the suspect in the murder of two #Arizona teens posted videos of himself firing a homemade semi-automatic weapon.
title: Chilling Video Shows Double Murder Suspect Thomas Brown Firing Gun #shorts
